The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, August 15, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, August 15, 2003				 																Independence Day				 																																	Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will hoist the Tricolour at Writers Buildings at 10.30 am.				 																																	A tribute to senior citizens with a ride on the heritage tram, Banalata, by the Rotary Club of Jodhpur Gardens and Calcutta Tramways Company, from Curzon Park, 8.30 am. V. Balsara and Ram Kumar Chattopadhyay will be present.				 																																	South Point School students will take out an environment awareness rally from Gol Park at 8.15 am. A cultural show and a performance by the Nature Club at 9.15 am in school.				 																																	A cultural evening with a dance performance by Debashree Roy, songs by Manasi Mukherjee, antakshari and an eastern food festival, at Swabhumi from 4.30 pm.				 																																	Monsoon Masti, featuring live performance by Shayne Hyrapiet, fashion show, model hunt and a party with Tollywood celebrities, at Fun City from 5 pm.				 																																	A sit-and-draw contest for children at My Montessori and Playhouse, at 6, Middle Road, from 10.30 am to 1 pm.				 																																	Freedom, an exhibition of art, at Galerie La Mere, at 3, Regent Park, from 6 pm.				 																Prize distribution				 																																	The prize distribution of The Telegraph Merchants Cup Badminton 2003 at Saturday Club from 8 pm.
